CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 21, 1963, pg. 5, reads: "Picket Steelworkers' Union - In a jurisdictional fight over the union membership of workers dismantling the old U. S. Steel mill in Donora, members of Local 178, Hod Carriers and Common Laborers Union, this week are picketing the downtown headquarters of the United Steel Workers. - Harris Photo."Signs read: "United Steel Workers of America taking work from laborers, Unfair to General Labor, Local Union 178 affiliated with AFL CIO"
TitMainTitle: Men from Local Union 178 protesting labor policy outside United Steelworkers headquarters, Commonwealth Building, Downtown
